ntifiable information (“Personal Information”) gathered when you are using or accessing the Services. This Privacy Policy also covers our treatment of any Personal Information that our business partners share with us or that we share with our business partners.<br><br>This Privacy Policy does not apply to the practices of third parties (“Third Party Services”) that we do not own or control. While to our best attempt, we only allow access to those Third Party Services that share our respect for your privacy, we cannot take responsibility for the privacy policies of those Third Party Services.<br><br>We will never knowingly solicit or accept Personal Information from users known to be under thirteen (13) years of age. If we learn that we have received any Personal Information from a user under 13 years of age, we will remove such Personal Information from our records.</span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-0298a200"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-644e0298">2. What information do you collect?<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-8b7b6327"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-1ce18b7b">The information we gather enables us to personalise, improve and continue to operate the Services. In connection with certain aspects of the Services, we may request, collect and/or display some of your Personal Information. We collect the following types of information from our users:<br><br><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Account information</span>. We collect personal information, such as your name, contact information, mailing address and financial information when you register for our Service, or otherwise communicate with us.<br><br><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">User-generated content</span>. Some features of the Services may allow you to provide content to the Services, such as written comments and testimonials. All content submitted by you to the Services may be retained by us indefinitely, even after you terminate your account. We may continue to disclose such content to third parties, as described in this Privacy Policy.<br><br><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Public Information</span>. It is important to note that some of your activity on and through the Services is public by default. For example, public product reviews, social media comment sections, and similar other platforms. If you choose to post your Personal Information through these public features, then that information may be publicly available. We therefore urge you to think carefully about including any information you deem private in content before submitting it through these features.<br><br><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">IP and cookies</span>. We automatically receive and record information from your web browser when you interact with the Services, including your IP address and cookie information. <br><br>Except as set forth above, you will be notified when your Personal Information may be shared with third parties, and will be able to prevent the sharing of this information.</span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-c4c266a4"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a810c4c2">3. For what purpose?<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-07e5544d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-bfde07e5"><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Fulfilling and shipping orders</span>. When you order products using the Services, we request and store your shipping information. We share this information with our third party payment processing company (the “Payment Processor”), fulfilment companies, partners and other third parties for purposes of customer service and order fulfilment. Use of your information by such parties is governed by their respective privacy policies.<br><br>We collect and store only very limited and encrypted access your financial information in order to process your transaction. Your financial information is collected and stored by our third party Payment Processor. Use and storage of that information is governed by the Payment Processor’s terms of service and privacy policy. We may from time to time request and receive some of your other financial information from our Payment Processor for the purposes of completing transactions you have initiated through the Services, enrolling you in discount or other programs in which you elect to participate, protecting against or identifying possible fraudulent transactions, and otherwise as needed to manage our business.<br><br><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Communications</span>. As part of the Services, you may occasionally receive email and other communications from us, such as promotional messages and communications relating to your Account. You may unsubscribe from promotional messages through your Account settings, although we, regardless, reserve the right to contact you when we believe it is necessary, such as for communications relating to your Account. We may also track your usage of and interaction with our emails, such as opens and clicks, in order to improve our Services.<br><br><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Improving our services</span>. Generally, the Services automatically collect usage information, such as the number and frequency of visitors to the Site, and we collect statistical information about how users use the Services (“Statistical Information”). This Statistical information may include Personal Information and we may also use this data in aggregate form. This type of data enables us and third parties authorised by us to figure out how often individuals use parts of the Services so that we can analyse and improve them. Our cookies do not, by themselves, contain Personal Information, and we do not combine the general information collected through cookies with other Personal Information to tell us